reviews.review_text: good stuff This AUD sounds friggin killer, and the Tom Thumb's sounds awesome. It is a very delicate and sublime version, not like the way they usually played it. There is a great April Fool's party type feel to this show!

Oade Sound Quality I never understood why people like the soundquality of these shows.

They sound flat, distant and with little bass.

Fun Run in Spring 85 Good times. Finally taking the time to really revisit this time period. Lot's of great aud's from this year and the Oade's were no slouches. I wouldn't say this recording sounds flat, if you know/like aud's give it a listen. Sounds crispy to me and pretty much captures the bands sound as I remember it for this time in these mid-size sheds. Pretty typical night of GD in 85. Solid perf. and worth the dl.

3 show.
4.5 for the recording.

strong disagreement with Utopian's assessment.  This AUD recording sounds better than many of the FMs from this period.  If it weren't for the lineage stated in the source material, I'd even question whether it was an AUD.  Just goes to show the Oades knew what they were doing.  5 stars to counter the effect of Utopian's 2.

Tom Foolery Well I was at this show and it was amazing that when it all was over and we came outside it was snowing. Man what a trip, I just found my ticket stub from this show, I payed a whole $11.50 We were having a high time and now Furthur we go keep on spilling we keep on gathering.

i was there in 85 iwas at this rockin show,iwas on and off the BUS,from 1973,till 91 when the sudo heads,got there,any way i drove up from ct in my old 72 buick, with my bro T.J { r.i.p.} but we hade a good ole time, idid have some reel strong doses that made it all good,i had herd dark star,st.steven,and now DAY TRIPER ,by the way that was half my life ago to-day,i do miss it so

maine shows always kick ass! I was at this show 84/85 were great years to be on tour.. ! 
the boys always rock Maine! one of the first times I heard Phil sing it was awesome! the whole let phil sing thing was going on then…the dead were still a way rocking intimate experience then…we were tripping balls, and after the show these  huge snowflakes were falling…and it was real , not the liquid…i got that confirmed.. :)
